&gt;&gt; Juan Felipe Herrera:
And the song,

00:15:12.510 --> 00:15:15.890
the song began back in third grade.

00:15:15.890 --> 00:15:22.130
I was in Logan Heights , San Diego
and I was always you know speaking

00:15:22.130 --> 00:15:25.670
in Spanish, that's my language
and I had been prohibited

00:15:25.670 --> 00:15:27.150
from speaking in Spanish.

00:15:27.150 --> 00:15:32.110 position:56%
And the day came when Mrs. Sampson,
Mrs. Lellia Sampson in Logan Heights

00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:36.960
in San Diego, California said,
"Come on up to the front, come on.

00:15:36.960 --> 00:15:41.860
Come on up and step to
the front and sing".

00:15:41.860 --> 00:15:44.980
And I said "I don't
know if I can do that".

00:15:44.980 --> 00:15:48.690 position:56%
To myself I said, "I don't think
so, no one has ever said that to me.

00:15:48.690 --> 00:15:52.510
No one has ever invited
me to the front, no one".

00:15:52.510 --> 00:15:53.960
So what does that mean?

00:15:53.960 --> 00:15:58.850
So I stepped up to the front
as best as I could and I sang,

00:15:58.850 --> 00:16:02.150
I sang Three Blind
Mice, the great opera.

00:16:02.150 --> 00:16:13.480
And then she turned to me and she
said, "You have a beautiful voice".

00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:21.380
And from that day on to this
very day, this very moment

00:16:21.380 --> 00:16:24.140
that was the key to my life.

00:16:24.140 --> 00:16:26.920
And I took that key
and I took those words

00:16:26.920 --> 00:16:30.080 position:56%
and I gave them to everyone I could.

00:16:30.080 --> 00:16:33.210
That's what she was
telling me that the beauty

00:16:33.210 --> 00:16:38.670
in my voice was the beauty
in everyone's voices.

00:16:38.670 --> 00:16:40.970
Yes.

